Articles.Content:
Like most i like to play with rovers but hate the limited gear and breaking but so far this is my most stable

rover on kerbin, havnt tried to fly it anywhere yet but it can get around nicely in atmo and full gravity. (175m/s)

Canards and RCS for great turning

<a target='_blank' title='ImageShack - Image And Video Hosting' href='http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/138/screenshot4js.png/'><img src='http://img138.imageshack.us/img138/1023/screenshot4js.png' border='0'/></a><br>Uploaded with <a target='_blank' href='http://imageshack.us'>ImageShack.us</a>

<a target='_blank' title='ImageShack - Image And Video Hosting' href='http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/713/screenshot2bv.png/'><img src='http://img713.imageshack.us/img713/7682/screenshot2bv.png' border='0'/></a><br>Uploaded with <a target='_blank' href='http://imageshack.us'>ImageShack.us</a>

When im going fast i use S to pull up on the nose with RSC this takes alot of the weight of the from gear and give you alot more speed and range without damage
